<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-970-464  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 970 464.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>UNIX Review  Dec 1989 v7 n12 p123(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Miller Freeman Publications 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Elegant Communications Inc. (Expert Remote System Assurancesupport service)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Elegant Communications Inc. (services).andO;Topic:     Support ServicesUNIXNetwork Management.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Elegant Communications Inc. A computer industry service company, ElegantCommunications Inc., has started a new UNIX system support service calledExpert Remote System Assurance (ERSA).andP;  It consists of an ERSA Monitorcomponent, which resides in client systems, which resides in client systems,performing audits and management activities, and ERSA Expert, which residesat the company's support facility, receiving and interpreting data from theMonitor.andP;  The Expert component prioritizes and presents data to the Monitor,giving immediate notification of urgent conditions, should they exist, andaccumulating data for weekly and monthly reports and histograms.andP;  The Monitorperforms automated security procedures, resources monitoring, housekeeping,network environment monitoring, recovery from service interruption, andapplication audit and support.andP;  The service is available for all UNIXvariants and hardware architectures.andM;ECI, Toronto, Ontario.andP;  416-595-5425.andO;</TEXT></DOC>